OL,7,FIt also found that when the last five
OL,8,Fbudgets are taken together, households
OL,9,Fare "slightly worse off" by about 0.7%
OL,10,Fof disposable income compared to a
OL,11,Fscenario of income-indexed budgets
OL,12,Fsince 2020.
OL,14,FWhen initiatives such as free
OL,15,Fschoolbooks and meals rolled out over
OL,16,Fthat period are taken into account,
OL,17,Fthe average loss was lower by just
OL,18,F0.3% of disposable income, showing
OL,19,Fthat non-cash benefits can have "a
OL,20,Fmeasurable impact" on incomes.
